{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566821","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566821"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:48:54+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:48:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18882"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18882","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18882"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.55,0.01,0.01,0.43,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11615"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96185"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11615","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11615"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18882"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78905"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"18"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11335"},{"type":"tags","id":"11336"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27336"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27337"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31828"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38906"},{"type":"contributions","id":"39286"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41896"},{"type":"contributions","id":"46064"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96185","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/96185"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA junior doctor notices that one of their colleagues frequently arrives late to handover meetings and leaves early, creating additional work for others. This has led to increasing tension within the team. The colleague becomes defensive when others have casually mentioned the issue.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial action to address this situation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Discuss specific concerns privately with the colleague","Send an email to all staff about punctuality","Request immediate reassignment to another team","Speak to your direct supervisor about the issue","Report the colleague directly to the medical board"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate initial action is to \u003Cstrong\u003Ediscuss specific concerns privately with the colleague\u003C/strong\u003E. This approach allows for direct communication while maintaining professionalism and giving the colleague an opportunity to explain their perspective and address any underlying issues.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect approaches are:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESend an email to all staff about punctuality\u003C/strong\u003E - Generic emails avoid addressing the specific issue and may be seen as passive-aggressive\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERequest immediate reassignment to another team\u003C/strong\u003E - This avoids addressing the underlying issue and may be disruptive to patient care\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESpeak to your direct supervisor about the issue\u003C/strong\u003E - While escalation may eventually be necessary, it should not be the first step before attempting direct communication\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReport the colleague directly to the medical board\u003C/strong\u003E - This is a disproportionate response for attendance issues that haven\u0027t yet been addressed directly\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe most effective approach to workplace conflict involves direct, respectful communication focused on specific behaviours rather than personal characteristics. If the initial discussion doesn\u0027t resolve the issue, then escalation to supervisors or other appropriate channels may be necessary.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Effective conflict resolution in healthcare requires identifying the underlying cause and addressing it directly with the involved parties.","Professional communication should focus on specific behaviours rather than personal characteristics.","Documentation of workplace conflicts should be objective, factual, and contemporaneous."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx","Australia Medical Association. Best practice approach to effective dispute resolution [online]. 2023. [Cited 2025 Jan 16]. Available at: https://www.ama.com.au/qld/disputeresolution"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78905"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18882"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78905","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/78905"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-31T16:11:49+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-31T16:13:28+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11615"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96185"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"18","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/18"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddd1\u200d\u2696\ufe0f","name":"Medicolegal","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":nu